title: Casino of Firmin Mitchel Roast Beef Corporation, Chinese Village, Hoo-Hoo House at Alaska Yukon Pacific Exposition, 1909
description: Transcribed from photograph: "Alaska Yukon Pacific Exposition. 1909. Casino of Firmin Mitchel Roast Beef Corporation. Wilcox and Sayward, architects. Chinese Village. Graham and Myers, architects. Hoo-hoo house. Ellsworth Storey, architect. Subsequently the Faculty Club, University of Washington."

title: King County Courthouse, 1886
description: Transcribed from front of photograph: "Buildings. King County Courthouse. Third Avenue and Jefferson Street. Built 1882; demolished after 1891. 1886." Transcribed from back of photograph: "The first courthouse of King County, at the corner of Jefferson Street and Third Avenue, built in 188_. The second store of the county jail appears on the right or south. Sold to the City of Seattle in 1891 and used since with many changes and additions for a City Hall. The house on the hill top is the dwelling of Beriah Brown, on Seventh Avenue and Terrace Street. Three blocks to the West is  the M. S. Booth dwelling."

title: Old Territorial University building in use by Seattle Public Library, ca. 1901
description: Transcribed from photograph: "Public Library. 1901-1906. Old University building used by Seattle Public Library 1901-1906. At first located at Fourth Ave. and Seneca St; in 1905 moved to Fifth Ave. and Union St. John Pike, architect."

title: View north from Pine St. and Terry Ave., 1907
description: Transcribed from photograph: "Views. From Pine St. and Terry Ave. 1907. Looking North."

title: George Washington Statue, ca. 1939
description: Transcribed from photograph: "Monuments. George Washington. Statue by Lorado Taft. University of Washington. Dedicated June 14, 1909 at the Alaska Yukon Pacific exposition. Moved to permanent base in 1939. This inscription was on the temporary pedestal as well as the present pedestal: Present to the University of Washington/ June 14, 1909, by the Rainier Chapter Daughters/ Of the American Revolution assisted by the school children of the State of Washington/ And by State commission of the Alaska Yukon/ Pacific exposition."
subjects: Daughters of the American Revolution. Rainier Chapter (Seattle, Wash.)
